=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Env_ex6 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 893 Hz, featuring slow attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, energy distribution is front_heavy, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: slow
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: front_heavy

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 892.7977
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.3412
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5136
  pitch_clarity: 6.1652
  inharmonicity: 0.4172
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -0.8118
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Env Example 6
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Env.html
// Tags: Env, Classes, envelope
// ---
// --- Example 6 ---
(
{
    var env = Env([0.0, 0.5, 0.0, 1.0, 0.9, 0.0], [0.05, 0.1, 0.01, 1.0, 1.5], -4);
    var envgen = EnvGen.ar(env, doneAction: Done.freeSelf);
    env.plot;
    SinOsc.ar(
        envgen * 1000 + 440
    ) * envgen * 0.1
}.play
);
